main event: A civilian reported a UFO sighting, which was later identified as the planet Venus, over Manning, North Dakota on 11-13 November 1961.
interesting points: The object was detected on ground radar for approximately 2 hours during clear weather conditions., The reported sighting occurred during a time when Venus was visible in the sky., There was no evidence that the object was anything other than a natural phenomenon., The observation was made at dawn, coinciding with the time of sighting of Venus., The observer was a 35-year-old farmer, and the report includes information about wind conditions and cloud cover.
sighted object: unidentified flying object, identified as the planet Venus
